value.value: An educational institution for children that precedes kindergarten.

A 24-item questionnaire designed to provide a comprehensive assessment of callous and unemotional traits. These traits have proven to be important for designating a distinct subgroup of antisocial and aggressive youth.
This gene is involved in linking the postsynaptic membrane to glutamate receptors.
Education or intervention aimed at individuals outside of a medical care system, especially those who might not otherwise have access to medical services.

Human SHANK2 wild-type allele is located within 11q13.3-q13.4 and is approximately 785 kb in length. This allele, which encodes SH3 and multiple ankyrin repeat domains protein 2, plays a role in postsynaptic signal transduction. Deletions and nonsense mutation of the gene may be associated with autism.
Education or intervention aimed at individuals within a medical care system.
Education or intervention aimed at individuals both outside of, and within a medical care system.

label.value: SH3 and Multiple Ankyrin Repeat Domains Protein 2

value.value: SH3 and multiple ankyrin repeat domains protein 2 (1470 aa, ~159 kDa) is encoded by the human SHANK2 gene. This protein is involved in organization of both the structure and function of the synaptic junction.
This gene plays a role in T-cell development.

Human TOX wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 8q12.1 and is approximately 314 kb in length. This allele, which encodes thymocyte selection-associated high mobility group box protein TOX, is involved in DNA binding and T-cell development.

label.value: Central Nervous System B-Cell Non-Hodgkin Lymphoma

value.value: A B-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma that arises from the brain, meninges, or spinal cord.

label.value: Pediatric Quality of Life Enjoyment and Satisfaction Questionnaire

value.value: A version of the Quality of Life Enjoyment and Satisfaction Questionnaire designed to assess changes in quality of life associated with treatment, as perceived by children and adolescents in the context of life events that are more meaningful in this population.

label.value: Thymocyte Selection-Associated High Mobility Group Box Protein TOX

value.value: Thymocyte selection-associated high mobility group box protein TOX (526 aa, ~58 kDa) is encoded by the human TOX gene. This protein plays a role in thymocyte development.
A radiologist that specializes in the use of minimally invasive image-guided procedures for the diagnosis and treatment of disease.
This gene is involved in inhibition of nuclear import of receptor-regulated SMADs (R-SMADs).

Human LEMD3 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 12q14.3 and is approximately 79 kb in length. This allele, which encodes inner nuclear membrane protein Man1, plays a role in the downregulation of transforming growth factor beta (TGF-B) receptor signaling. Mutations in the gene have been associated with osteopoikilosis, Buschke-Ollendorff syndrome and melorheostosis.

Inner nuclear membrane protein Man1 (911 aa, ~100 kDa) is encoded by the human LEMD3 gene. This protein is involved in the negative regulation of transforming growth factor beta (TGF-B) receptor signaling.
This gene plays a role in environmental stress-activated signaling pathways.

Human MAP3K4 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6q26 and is approximately 126 kb in length. This allele, which encodes mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase kinase 4 protein, is involved in signaling stimulated by environmental stressors.
Mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase kinase 4 (1608 aa, ~182 kDa) is encoded by the human MAP3K4 gene. This protein plays a role in stress induced signaling pathways.

label.value: The Screen for Child Anxiety Related Emotional Disorders

value.value: A 41-item, self- or parent-report questionnaire designed to screen for childhood anxiety disorders, including general anxiety disorder, separation anxiety disorder, panic disorder, social phobia, and symptoms related to school phobias in children aged 8-17.

A 90-item self-report symptom inventory designed to measure psychological symptoms and psychological distress for individuals 13 years and older. It is intended to measure symptom intensity on nine different subscales.

A 13-item, self-administered questionnaire designed to meassure depressive symptoms. The MFQ consists of a series of descriptive phrases regarding how the subject has been feeling or acting recently and is a screening tool for depression in children and young people aged between 6 and 17 years.
This gene is involved in the transcription of ribosomal RNA genes.

Human UBTF wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17q21.31 and is approximately 17 kb in length. This allele, which encodes nucleolar transcription factor 1 protein, plays a role in ribosomal RNA synthesis. Mutation of the gene is associated with childhood-onset neurodegeneration with brain atrophy (CONDBA).
Nucleolar transcription factor 1 (764 aa, ~89 kDa) is encoded by the human UBTF gene. This protein is involved in the positive regulation of ribosomal RNA gene transcription.

label.value: Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, 5th Edition

value.value: Published by the American Psychiatric Association, the DSM is a listing of currently recognized mental health disorders and their diagnostic criteria, for children and adults. It includes statistical information on etiology, incidence, prevalence, age of onset and prognosis. The 5th edition was published in 2013. As new information becomes available subsequent editions are published.
Breast carcinoma that does not respond to treatment.
This gene plays a role in the negative regulation of cell proliferation.

Human TUSC7 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 3q13.31 and is approximately 14 kb in length. This allele, which encodes tumor suppressor candidate 7 long non-coding RNA, is involved in the modulation of cell proliferation.
Tumor suppressor candidate 7 (~2 kb) is encoded by the human TUSC7 gene. This long non-coding RNA plays a role in the downregulation of cell proliferation.
This gene is involved in neurotransmitter-dependent chloride transport.

Human GABRA6 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 5q34 and is approximately 156 kb in length. This allele, which encodes gamma-aminobutyric acid receptor subunit alpha-6 protein, plays a role in chloride conductance.
Gamma-aminobutyric acid receptor subunit alpha-6 (453 aa, ~51 kDa) is encoded by the human GABRA6 gene. This protein is involved in ligand-gated chloride transport.
This gene plays a role in the ubiquitination of gluconeogenic enzymes.

Human GID4 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17p11.2 and is approximately 29 kb in length. This allele, which encodes glucose-induced degradation protein 4 homolog, is involved in the degradation of gluconeogenic enzymes.
Glucose-induced degradation protein 4 homolog (300 aa, ~34 kDa) is encoded by the human GID4 gene. This protein plays a role in the ubiquitination and proteasomal targeting of gluconeogenic enzymes.
This gene is involved in glomerulus development.

Human PTPRO wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 12p12.3 and is approximately 276 kb in length. This allele, which encodes receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase O protein, plays a role in both glomerulus development and protein tyrosine phosphatase activity. Mutation of the gene may be associated with nephrotic syndrome.
Receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase O (1216 aa, ~138 kDa) is encoded by the human PTPRO gene. This protein is involved in tyrosine phosphatase activity and glomerular epithelium development.
This gene plays a role in the ADP-ribosylation of proteins involved in base excision repair.

Human PARP3 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 3p21.2 and is approximately 7 kb in length. This allele, which encodes protein mono-ADP-ribosyltransferase PARP3 protein, is involved in the regulation of DNA base excision repair.
Protein mono-ADP-ribosyltransferase PARP3 (533 aa, ~60 kDa) is encoded by the human PARP3 gene. This protein plays a role in DNA repair and mono-ADP-ribosylation of target proteins.

Therapy in which a therapist, or other personnel, provides nondirective, supportive care by offering supportive, validating statements and reflective listening. Verbal support sessions are aimed at providing an empathic, therapeutic environment to facilitate emotional expression and sharing of worries and fears.
Colorectal carcinoma that does not respond to treatment.
